{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":914,"text":"I suspect that"},{"time":2323,"text":"every aid worker in Africa"},{"time":4080,"text":"comes to a time in her career"},{"time":5673,"text":"when she wants to take all \nthe money for her project —"},{"time":8989,"text":"maybe it's a school or a training program —"},{"time":12091,"text":"pack it in a suitcase,"},{"time":13980,"text":"get on a plane flying over the\npoorest villages in the country,"},{"time":17964,"text":"and start throwing that money out the window."},{"time":21148,"text":"Because to a veteran aid worker,"},{"time":23464,"text":"the idea of putting cold, hard cash"},{"time":26171,"text":"into the hands of the poorest people on Earth"},{"time":29210,"text":"doesn't sound crazy,"},{"time":30865,"text":"it sounds really satisfying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34941,"text":"I had that moment right about the 10-year mark,"},{"time":37843,"text":"and luckily, that's also when I learned"},{"time":40310,"text":"that this idea actually exists,"},{"time":43974,"text":"and it might be just what the aid system needs."},{"time":47817,"text":"Economists call it an unconditional cash transfer,"},{"time":50520,"text":"and it's exactly that: It's cash given"},{"time":52680,"text":"with no strings attached."},{"time":54952,"text":"Governments in developing countries"},{"time":56516,"text":"have been doing this for decades,"},{"time":58192,"text":"and it's only now, with more evidence"},{"time":60724,"text":"and new technology that it's possible"},{"time":63915,"text":"to make this a model for delivering aid."},{"time":68234,"text":"It's a pretty simple idea, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":71148,"text":"Well, why did I spend a decade doing other stuff"},{"time":75254,"text":"for the poor?"},{"time":77392,"text":"Honestly, I believed that I could do more good"},{"time":80935,"text":"with money for the poor"},{"time":82881,"text":"than the poor could do for themselves."},{"time":85491,"text":"I held two assumptions:"},{"time":86524,"text":"One, that poor people are poor in part"},{"time":89113,"text":"because they're uneducated and"},{"time":91115,"text":"don't make good choices;"},{"time":93275,"text":"two is that we then need people like me"},{"time":95986,"text":"to figure out what they need and get it to them."},{"time":99724,"text":"It turns out, the evidence says otherwise."},{"time":103946,"text":"In recent years, researchers have been studying"},{"time":106795,"text":"what happens when we give poor people cash."},{"time":110200,"text":"Dozens of studies show across the board"},{"time":112871,"text":"that people use cash transfers"},{"time":115627,"text":"to improve their own lives."},{"time":117795,"text":"Pregnant women in Uruguay buy better food"},{"time":120643,"text":"and give birth to healthier babies."},{"time":122877,"text":"Sri Lankan men invest in their businesses."},{"time":125971,"text":"Researchers who studied our work in Kenya"},{"time":128669,"text":"found that people invested in a range of assets,"},{"time":131586,"text":"from livestock to equipment \nto home improvements,"},{"time":135936,"text":"and they saw increases in income"},{"time":138058,"text":"from business and farming"},{"time":140441,"text":"one year after the cash was sent."},{"time":144131,"text":"None of these studies found that people"},{"time":146695,"text":"spend more on drinking or smoking"},{"time":149104,"text":"or that people work less."},{"time":151609,"text":"In fact, they work more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155717,"text":"Now, these are all material needs."},{"time":158980,"text":"In Vietnam, elderly recipients used"},{"time":162151,"text":"their cash transfers to pay for coffins."},{"time":166662,"text":"As someone who wonders if Maslow got it wrong,"},{"time":170673,"text":"I find this choice to prioritize spiritual needs"},{"time":175400,"text":"deeply humbling."},{"time":177667,"text":"I don't know if I would have chosen to give food"},{"time":179880,"text":"or equipment or coffins,"},{"time":183491,"text":"which begs the question:"},{"time":185781,"text":"How good are we at allocating resources"},{"time":188777,"text":"on behalf of the poor?"},{"time":190622,"text":"Are we worth the cost?"},{"time":193517,"text":"Again, we can look at empirical evidence"},{"time":195460,"text":"on what happens when we give people stuff"},{"time":198250,"text":"of our choosing."},{"time":200926,"text":"One very telling study looked at a program in India"},{"time":203795,"text":"that gives livestock to the so-called ultra-poor,"},{"time":207102,"text":"and they found that 30 percent of recipients"},{"time":211023,"text":"had turned around and sold the\nlivestock they had been given"},{"time":215176,"text":"for cash."},{"time":218529,"text":"The real irony is,"},{"time":220087,"text":"for every 100 dollars worth of assets"},{"time":222668,"text":"this program gave someone,"},{"time":224820,"text":"they spent another 99 dollars to do it."},{"time":229506,"text":"What if, instead, we use technology to put cash,"},{"time":233152,"text":"whether from aid agencies or from any one of us"},{"time":237739,"text":"directly into a poor person's hands."},{"time":241509,"text":"Today, three in four Kenyans use mobile money,"},{"time":244379,"text":"which is basically a bank account that can run"},{"time":247202,"text":"on any cell phone."},{"time":248700,"text":"A sender can pay a 1.6 percent fee"},{"time":252166,"text":"and with the click of a button"},{"time":254204,"text":"send money directly to a recipient's account"},{"time":257155,"text":"with no intermediaries."},{"time":259885,"text":"Like the technologies that are disrupting industries"},{"time":262748,"text":"in our own lives,"},{"time":264547,"text":"payments technology in poor countries"},{"time":267110,"text":"could disrupt aid."},{"time":270217,"text":"It's spreading so quickly that it's possible"},{"time":272529,"text":"to imagine reaching billions"},{"time":275061,"text":"of the world's poor this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277860,"text":"That's what we've started to do at GiveDirectly."},{"time":280481,"text":"We're the first organization"},{"time":282146,"text":"dedicated to providing cash transfers to the poor."},{"time":285319,"text":"We've sent cash to 35,000 \npeople across rural Kenya"},{"time":289987,"text":"and Uganda"},{"time":291154,"text":"in one-time payments of 1,000 dollars"},{"time":294332,"text":"per family."},{"time":296917,"text":"So far, we've looked for the poorest people"},{"time":299177,"text":"in the poorest villages, and in this part of the world,"},{"time":302480,"text":"they're the ones living in homes"},{"time":303924,"text":"made of mud and thatch,"},{"time":305102,"text":"not cement and iron."},{"time":307562,"text":"So let's say that's your family."},{"time":309784,"text":"We show up at your door with an Android phone."},{"time":312236,"text":"We'll get your name, take your photo"},{"time":314563,"text":"and a photo of your hut"},{"time":315979,"text":"and grab the GPS coordinates."},{"time":318454,"text":"That night, we send all the data to the cloud,"},{"time":320554,"text":"and each piece gets checked"},{"time":322834,"text":"by an independent team"},{"time":324712,"text":"using, for one example, satellite images."},{"time":328103,"text":"Then, we'll come back,"},{"time":330099,"text":"we'll sell you a basic cell phone"},{"time":332490,"text":"if you don't have one already,"},{"time":334757,"text":"and a few weeks later,"},{"time":337078,"text":"we send money to it."},{"time":339369,"text":"Something that five years ago"},{"time":340930,"text":"would have seemed impossible"},{"time":342458,"text":"we can now do efficiently"},{"time":345343,"text":"and free of corruption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347481,"text":"The more cash we give to the poor,"},{"time":349797,"text":"and the more evidence we have that it works,"},{"time":353453,"text":"the more we have to reconsider"},{"time":355861,"text":"everything else we give."},{"time":358350,"text":"Today, the logic behind aid is too often,"},{"time":361938,"text":"well, we do at least some good."},{"time":365050,"text":"When we're complacent"},{"time":366466,"text":"with that as our bar,"},{"time":368836,"text":"when we tell ourselves that giving aid"},{"time":371428,"text":"is better than no aid at all,"},{"time":374342,"text":"we tend to invest inefficiently,"},{"time":376614,"text":"in our own ideas that strike us as innovative,"},{"time":380596,"text":"on writing reports,"},{"time":382750,"text":"on plane tickets and SUVs."},{"time":386596,"text":"What if the logic was,"},{"time":388920,"text":"will we do better than cash given directly?"},{"time":394191,"text":"Organizations would have to prove"},{"time":395701,"text":"that they're doing more good for the poor"},{"time":397930,"text":"than the poor can do for themselves."},{"time":400686,"text":"Of course, giving cash won't create public goods"},{"time":403634,"text":"like eradicating disease or \nbuilding strong institutions,"},{"time":408952,"text":"but it could set a higher bar"},{"time":411178,"text":"for how we help individual families"},{"time":414140,"text":"improve their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417166,"text":"I believe in aid."},{"time":418729,"text":"I believe most aid is better than just"},{"time":421828,"text":"throwing money out of a plane."},{"time":423740,"text":"I am also absolutely certain"},{"time":426288,"text":"that a lot of aid today"},{"time":428521,"text":"isn't better than giving directly to the poor."},{"time":432046,"text":"I hope that one day, it will be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435922,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437978,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}